ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a course teaching you the basic concepts and application of the core topics in biomedical informatics.Yes, I will recommend this course to other students.

Yes. CBB students have different backgrounds - either biology or computer science. We can see how cs help us get more meaningful biological meaning and also how cs can applies to biological discipline.
It is required for CBB, so not much choice here.Would not recommend for non-CBB: the treatment of material is too superficial.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: As I said before, this course deepens my knowledge very much, esp. in database part.

I was given a broad overview of computational biology and bioinformatics, though I did not realize this until the last week of the course; I noticed that at the end of the course when people asked me to describe my major I was having much less trouble as a result of the class. However, since the course is so broad, it doesn't seem like it will have a direct contribution to my research.
Provided a good overview of the field. Provided some insights into what direction I would like to take my research.
